      <meta name="description" content="I noted this when testing the changes for lxd:isolated in Ubuntu Xenial; neutron sets up iptables rules against tap devices (as used in the libvirt driver); however nova-lxd does not use tap devices - LXD plumbs the instance in to the neutron bridge using an veth pair.

I think the net result of this is that security rules are just not getting applied in LXD instances." />
      <meta property="og:description" content="I noted this when testing the changes for lxd:isolated in Ubuntu Xenial; neutron sets up iptables rules against tap devices (as used in the libvirt driver); however nova-lxd does not use tap devices - LXD plumbs the instance in to the neutron bridge using an veth pair.

I think the net result of this is that security rules are just not getting applied in LXD instances." />
    

    
    
