    <h3>Bug Description</h3>
  </div>

  <div class="yui3-editable_text-text"><p>I noted this when testing the changes for lxd:isolated in Ubuntu Xenial; neutron sets up iptables rules against tap devices (as used in the libvirt driver); however nova-lxd does not use tap devices - LXD plumbs the instance in to the neutron bridge using an veth pair.</p>
<p>I think the net result of this is that security rules are just not getting applied in LXD instances.</p></div>
